Define a function that takes no parameters and prints “Hello.”

Write a function that accepts two integers and returns their sum.

Demonstrate an expression without a semicolon versus a statement.

Pass a string slice to a function and print its length.

Create a function with a return type annotation.

Call one function from another and observe scope rules.

Use a function to return a tuple of two values.

Explain the difference between () and returning a value.

Define a function inside another scope (nested).

Illustrate the compiler error for a mismatched return type.
